Minjurochong vows solidarity struggle 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The South Korean Confederation of Trade Unions (Minjurochong) held a press conference on September 6  amidst worsening confrontation with the airline company side regarding the issue of establishing a pilots union in South Korea and expressed its will to wage a powerful solidarity struggle, according to a radio report from Seoul.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minjurochong said that the "government" and the company side were disturbing the setup of the pilots union and it would continue a powerful struggle in solidarity with the crew until its demand is met.

Work of Kim Jong Il published in book form abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The famous work of General Secretary Kim Jong Il "Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully through the Great Unity of the Entire Nation" was published in booklet by the Heritage Publishing House of Trinidad and Tobago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The work is a letter sent on April 18 last year to a national symposium marking the 50th anniversary of the historic joint conference of representatives of political parties and public organizations in north and south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The letter clarified the five-point policy of great national unity -- to maintain the principle of national independence, unite under the banner of patriotism, improve inter-Korean relations, struggle against the domination of the foreign forces and the anti-reunification forces and strengthen solidarity through contacts and dialogue of the whole nation.

Loving care shown for heroine Jong Song Ok
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Jong Song Ok, who is praised as the nation's praiseworthy daughter and the world's "queen of marathon," enjoys highest honor and greatest happiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Jong Song Ok is a marathoner of the Amnokgang Sports Group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She defeated top-notch runners in the women's marathon race of the 7th World Athletics Championships in Seville, Spain on August 29 and took the world title, thus demonstrating the dignity and spirit of the Korean nation all over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  General Secretary Kim Jong Il has granted all special privileges and benefits to the marathoner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She received a gold wrist watch inscribed with the august name of the President Kim Il Sung and gifts sent by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   She was awarded the title of DPRK heroine as well as the Title of People's Sportswoman. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Kim Jong Il made sure that a deluxe car was presented to her, saying that nothing should be spared for the "queen of marathon", who demonstrated the wisdom and mettle of the nation to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He provided her and her family with a deluxe flat furnished with all kinds of furniture and kitchen utensils, as a real father would do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Upon her return home, she was given an unheard-of enthusiastic welcome by more than one million Pyongyangites along the more than 10 kilometre-long route. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A state banquet, a meeting of Pyongyangites, an evening gala of school youth and children and performances of the Wangjaesan Light Music Band and schoolchildren were arranged in her honor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Indeed, the world's "queen of marathon", Jong Song Ok, is blessed with the greatest honor and happiness a sportswoman can ever enjoy.

National sports contest of workers
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A national sports contest of workers was held in Pyongyang on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The contest involved basketball, football, volleyball and hurdle race with the participation of hundreds of players sifted out from preliminaries in provinces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the total standings, players of Pyongyang placed first, those of North Hamgyong  Province second and those of Kangwon Province and South Hwanghae Province third.

Performances and evening gala celebrate DPRK  birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Art performances were given and an evening gala of Pyongyang youth and students took place on September 9, the 51st anniversary of the foundation of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Art performances and music concerts were given by different art troupes at theatres in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The performances were appreciated by Kim Yong Nam, Paek Hak Rim, Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop and other senior party and state officials, a congratulatory group of Korean residents in Japan and overseas. Koreans and the chief of the Pyongyang mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present on invitation were foreign delegations, foreign diplomatic envoys and embassy officials here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The performers paid highest tribute to the President Kim Il Sung who founded the DPRK and demonstrated its dignity and might to the whole world, and represented well the will and determination of the Korean people to build a powerful nation under General Secretary Kim Jong Il, holding him in high esteem. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Colorful art performances were also given at all provincial theatres including the Hamhung grand theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   An evening gala of Pyongyang youth and students took place at the Kim Il Sung Square. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The participants presented merry dances to the strains of music of "Song of the Proclamation of the People's Republic," "Let national flag of the republic, our tricolor flag, flutter," "Song of the People's Power" and so on.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Overseas Koreans and foreign friends enjoyed the evening, dancing with youth and students.

DPRK government gives reception on its foundation day
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The government of the DPRK gave a reception at Okryu Restaurant on Sept. 9 on the occasion of the 51st anniversary of its foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the reception were Kim Yong Nam, Hong Song Nam, other senior party and state officials, members of the congratulatory group of Korean residents in Japan for celebrating the 51st anniversary of the founding of the DPRK led by Kwon Sun Hwi, vice-chairman of the central standing committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, overseas Koreans and Pak Kwang Gi, chief of the Pyongyang mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Foreign envoys here, representatives of international organizations and foreign guests were also invited. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Yang Hyong Sop, vice-President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, made a speech at the reception. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Noting that the DPRK government has successfully carried out its mission and role as a powerful weapon in the revolution and construction under the wise leadership of the party and the leader, he said under the banner of the republic the Korean people have heroically overcome all sorts of difficulties and trials and recorded a new history of great epoch-making changes and prosperity in the annals of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Though the DPRK is confronted with an unprecedentedly complicated and tense situation at home and abroad, and the road of revolution ahead of us remains arduous and thorny, the victory is in store for us, he said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This is well illustrated by the fact that thanks to the outstanding army first policy of the great Kim Jong Il, the gifted thinker and theoretician, the great master of leadership and the ever-victorious iron-willed brilliant commander, the DPRK's might is growing stronger day by day and all the moves of the imperialists to isolate and stifle the DPRK are being frustrated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S., Japanese warmongers and the South Korean authorities are becoming more undisguised in their moves to provoke a new war against the DPRK. We intend to answer good faith with good faith and dialogue with dialogue, but we will never pardon the acts of infringing  upon our sovereignty even a little. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Korean people and people's army will more vigorously accelerate the second grand Chollima march under the banner of the three revolutions, ideological, technical and cultural through the perfect army-people unity, upholding the revolutionary army-first leadership of the great Kim Jong Il and thus accomplish the cause of building a powerful socialist nation and certainly achieve the historic cause of national reunification.

Release of S. Korean reunification organizations demanded
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- Ri Jong Hwal, chairman of the Association of  Koreans in Japan for Peaceful Reunification released a statement on September 7, denouncing the South Korean authorities for arresting the delegates of reunification organizations, who participated in the grand pan-national reunification festival this year, on the charge of violating the "National Security Law". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   In the statement he condemned the South Korean authorities for their anti-national and anti-reunification criminal act.     &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said that during their visit to the DPRK the delegates called for the independence and great unity of the nation and reunification by a confederal formula, representing the will of compatriots in the south for reunification. This is not a crime but a patriotic deed, he pointed out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He stressed he keenly realized once again that the reunification movement cannot make even a step forward without a struggle against the outside and anti-reunification forces which block the independence and great unity of the nation.     &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He expressed his firm will to conduct a dynamic movement for reunification, keeping step with the South Korean patriotic organizations in the struggle for the release of the pro-reunification patriots.

Monument to three charters of national reunification
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The monument to the three charters of national reunification is under construction in peculiar style at the hilly left side of the entrance to Pyongyang from Kaesong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Its plottage covers about  20,000 square meters and the monument is 55 meters high. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The monument will make  a formative and artistic representation of the three charters of national reunification set forth by the President Kim Il Sung and established by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The three charters consist of three principles of national reunification--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--the proposal on founding the Democratic Confederal Republic of Koryo and the 10-point program for the great unity of the entire nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The monument portrays a "maypole," a dance on the theme of national unity performed during the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It will have a central pillar depicting a main pole and three leaning branch poles that support the main pole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There will be at the top of the pillar a solid sphere where a golden-colored Korean map will be carved in relief. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The pedestal of the pillar will be inscribed with the content of the three charters and the space from it to the central pillar with the letters "monument to three charters of national reunification." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This reflects the aspiration of the Korean people in the north, south and abroad to reunify the country under the banner of the three charters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Grey granite will be used to erect the monument and a plaza around the monument be paved with granite. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A ground breaking ceremony took place here on August 14.

Japan cannot see in 21st century without difficulty
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The statement of the DPRK government which accused Japan of its 100-year-long history of criminal policy toward Korea and clarified its principled stand toward the DPRK-Japan relations is evoking lively repercussions internationally. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The statement, which was issued a month ago, declared that Japan cannot see in the 21st century without any difficulty as long as the present state of the relations with the DPRK remains unsettled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It urged the Japanese authorities to give up their hostile policy toward the DPRK, totally liquidate the past crimes and make a new policy switchover. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   This just call is warmly welcomed and supported by the international public circles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   No sooner had the DPRK government statement been issued than mass media of China, Cuba, Russia, Germany and many other countries of the world quoted the DPRK government statement as saying Japan must repent of and review the 100-year-long history of criminal policy toward Korea and make a new policy switchover. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Honorary Chairman of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, the general secretary of the central committee of the New Communist Party of Great Britain, the general secretary of the Good Green Guyana, international organizations and other public figures of different countries in a special statement published in Pyongyang said that all the international and regional organizations supporting peace and reunification of Korea and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people in all countries of the world will join them in the relentless just struggle to demand the Japanese authorities make an apology and compensation and to expose and denounce their anti-DPRK confrontation moves till they liquidate their past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The secretariat of the Council of the Union of Communist Parties-the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, 6 progressive political parties of Madagascar, the Maurice Bishop Patriotic Movement of Grenada, the Communist Party of Malta and other political parties and public organizations of a number of countries issued statements in which they urged Japan to take a reasonable and correct option to liquidate its crime-ridden past within this century at this historic moment when a new century of civilization is at hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and students of Peru, chairman of the Communist Party of Bulgaria (Marxist-Leninist), the chief of Information of the Permanent Secretariat of Organization of the Socialists in the Mediterranean and other figures in different countries and regions stressed in their statements that the Japanese authorities should not stretch the liquidation of its inglorious past into the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   As evidenced by a protest letter sent to the Japanese Prime Minister by the Left Democratic Front and several other organizations of Bangladesh in their joint name, an international opinion is growing stronger to demand the Japanese authorities ponder over and make a policy switchover as noted in the DPRK government statement.
